headline: Estée Lauder Conviction Raises Questions On Compliance Risks And Valuation
summary: Estée Lauder Companies (NYSE:EL) was convicted in Canada for selling eyeliners that contained banned forever chemicals. Estée Lauder is required to notify its shareholders of the conviction as part of its disclosure obligations. headline: Wall Street ticks lower before the bell and bitcoin slumps as markets sense broader risk

headline: Estée Lauder (EL) Q2 2026 Earnings Call Transcript
summary: When we introduced Beauty Reimagine, our ambition was bold, execute the biggest operational leadership, and cultural transformation in our history, to become the best consumer-centric prestige beauty company.  In 2026, our global retail sales trend improved from the first to the second quarter, from down 4% to flat as the decline in travel moderated.  In Mainland China, we outperformed Prestige Beauty in the quarter again with double-digit growth.

content.title: Estée Lauder (EL) Q2 2026 Earnings Call Transcript
content.summary: When we introduced Beauty Reimagine, our ambition was bold, execute the biggest operational leadership, and cultural transformation in our history, to become the best consumer-centric prestige beauty company. In Mainland China, we outperformed Prestige Beauty in the quarter again with double-digit growth.
